data.desc:
 Data array of series, which can be a single data value, like: 

    [12, 34, 56, 10, 23]


Or, if need extra dimensions for components like [visualMap][0] to map to graphic attributes like color, it can also be in the form of array. For example: 

    [[12, 14], [34, 50], [56, 30], [10, 15], [23, 10]]


In this case, we can assgin the second value in each array item to [visualMap][0] component. More likely, we need to assign name to each data item, in which case each item should be an object: 

    [{
        // name of date item
        name: 'data1',
        // value of date item is 8
        value: 10
    }, {
        name: 'data2',
        value: 20
    }]


Each data item can be further customized: 

    [{
        name: 'data1',
        value: 10
    }, {
        // name of data item
        name: 'data2',
        value : 56,
        // user-defined label format that only useful for this data item
        label: {},
        // user-defined special itemStyle that only useful for this data item
        itemStyle:{}
    }]




